	   <tr><td colspan=2>Range is bow range + arrow range.If you want to test this, root a mob then back up untill you move out of bow range.move back into range one step at a time till you start to shoot again. Take the arrows out of your ammo slot and shoot. You get the message that you are out of range. Move closer untill you are in bow range and you get the message you are out of ammo. You will not get the damage messages at extreme range. I have one of the new 200 range bows and with the new arrows i can hit well outside aggro range, or casting range. Max distance for a spell i believe is 200. I love the range it have means on a pull, i can get 2 or three shots off before the mob gets close enough to hit.What bow are you using that hits for an average of 25? I have an archery skill of 200 and still about half my shots don't even hit.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Mar&nbsp;&nbsp;7 20:02:28 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>Ranger of Tunare<br>Officer of SOotP<br>The Rathe</td></tr>
